Wash and dry all produce. Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Trim and thinly slice
@Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Core, deseed, and dice
@Poblano Pepper{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, 1 tsp
@Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} (2 tsp for 4 servings; you'll use the
rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture
reaches a drizzling consistency. In a separate small bowl, combine tomato,
scallion whites, and 1 TBSP @Green Salsa{7.06%ounce} (you'll use the rest
later). Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add poblano and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring,
until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @Ground Pork{10%ounce} and another drizzle of oil to same pan. Season with
salt, pepper, and remaining Southwest Spice. Cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until pork is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Add remaining green salsa to pan with pork; bring to a simmer over medium-high
heat. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in
@Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. Season with salt and
pepper. Turn off heat.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Divide tortillas between plates and fill with pork
mixture, @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}, salsa, and crema. Sprinkle with
scallion greens and serve.